prefix_rule(pattern=["/bin/zsh", "-lc", "cd /home/ryjen/Projects/micrantha/laboratory && cat <<'EOF' > terraform/modules/incus/instance/main.tf\nlocals {\n  effective_profiles = length(var.profiles) > 0 ? var.profiles : [\"default\"]\n}\n\nresource \"incus_instance\" \"this\" {\n  name              = var.name\n  project           = var.project\n  image             = var.image\n  architecture      = var.architecture\n  type              = var.instance_type\n  profiles          = local.effective_profiles\n  config            = var.config\n  limits            = var.limits\n  ephemeral         = var.ephemeral\n  wait_for_network  = var.wait_for_network\n\n  dynamic \"device\" {\n    for_each = var.devices\n    content {\n      name       = device.value.name\n      type       = device.value.type\n      properties = device.value.properties\n    }\n  }\n}\nEOF"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["/bin/zsh", "-lc", "cd /home/ryjen/Projects/micrantha/laboratory && cat <<'EOF' > terraform/modules/incus/instance/outputs.tf\noutput \"id\" {\n  description = \"Incus-assigned UUID for the instance.\"\n  value       = incus_instance.this.id\n}\n\noutput \"name\" {\n  description = \"Configured instance name.\"\n  value       = incus_instance.this.name\n}\n\noutput \"type\" {\n  description = \"Instance type returned by the provider.\"\n  value       = incus_instance.this.type\n}\n\noutput \"project\" {\n  description = \"Project the instance lives in.\"\n  value       = incus_instance.this.project\n}\n\noutput \"profiles\" {\n  description = \"Profiles attached to the instance.\"\n  value       = incus_instance.this.profiles\n}\n\noutput \"networks\" {\n  description = \"Network interfaces and addresses exposed by the instance.\"\n  value       = incus_instance.this.networks\n}\nEOF"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["/bin/zsh", "-lc", "cd /home/ryjen/Projects/micrantha/laboratory && cat <<'EOF' > terraform/modules/incus/instance/README.md\n# Incus instance module\n\nThis module exposes the `incus_instance` resource from `lxc/incus` while keeping the calling layer focused on the values that change per deployment: image, profiles, devices, and resource limits.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Terraform `>= 1.5`\n- Provider `lxc/incus >= 1.0`\n\n## Example\n\n```hcl\nmodule \"control_plane\" {\n  source = \"../../modules/incus/instance\"\n\n  name           = \"micrantha-control\"\n  project        = \"default\"\n  image          = \"images:ubuntu/24.04\"\n  architecture   = \"x86_64\"\n  instance_type  = \"virtual-machine\"\n  profiles       = [\"default\"]\n  wait_for_network = true\n  limits = {\n    cpu    = 2\n    memory = \"4GiB\"\n  }\n  devices = [\n    {\n      name       = \"eth0\"\n      type       = \"nic\"\n      properties = {\n        nictype = \"bridged\"\n        parent  = \"lxdbr0\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      name       = \"root\"\n      type       = \"disk\"\n      properties = {\n        path = \"/\"\n        pool = \"default\"\n        size = \"30GiB\"\n      }\n    },\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nUse the `config` map to pass cloud-init fields or other low-level tweaks:\n\n```hcl\nconfig = {\n  \"cloud-init.user-data\" = <<EOF\n#cloud-config\npackages:\n  - htop\nEOF\n}\n```\nEOF"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["/bin/zsh", "-lc", "cd /home/ryjen/Projects/micrantha/laboratory && cat <<'DOC' > terraform/modules/incus/instance/README.md\n# Incus instance module\n\nThis module exposes the `incus_instance` resource from `lxc/incus` while keeping the calling layer focused on the values that change per deployment: image, profiles, devices, and resource limits.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Terraform `>= 1.5`\n- Provider `lxc/incus >= 1.0`\n\n## Example\n\n```hcl\nmodule \"control_plane\" {\n  source = \"../../modules/incus/instance\"\n\n  name            = \"micrantha-control\"\n  project         = \"default\"\n  image           = \"images:ubuntu/24.04\"\n  architecture    = \"x86_64\"\n  instance_type   = \"virtual-machine\"\n  profiles        = [\"default\"]\n  wait_for_network = true\n  limits = {\n    cpu    = 2\n    memory = \"4GiB\"\n  }\n  devices = [\n    {\n      name       = \"eth0\"\n      type       = \"nic\"\n      properties = {\n        nictype = \"bridged\"\n        parent  = \"lxdbr0\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      name       = \"root\"\n      type       = \"disk\"\n      properties = {\n        path = \"/\"\n        pool = \"default\"\n        size = \"30GiB\"\n      }\n    },\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nUse the `config` map to pass cloud-init fields or other low-level tweaks:\n\n```hcl\nconfig = {\n  \"cloud-init.user-data\" = <<'CONFIG'\n#cloud-config\npackages:\n  - htop\nCONFIG\n}\n```\nDOC"], decision="allow")
prefix_rule(pattern=["/bin/zsh", "-lc", "cd /home/ryjen/Projects/micrantha/laboratory && python - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\npath = Path('terraform/README.md')\ntext = path.read_text()\nold = \"- `libvirt/server`: This module creates a VM with Libvirt.\\n- `cloud-init`: This module contains the cloud-init configuration for the servers.\\n\"\nif old not in text:\n    raise SystemExit('pattern not found')\nnew = \"- `libvirt/server`: This module creates a VM with Libvirt.\\n- `incus/instance`: This module creates an LXC/Incus instance for local lab workloads.\\n- `cloud-init`: This module contains the cloud-init configuration for the servers.\\n\"\npath.write_text(text.replace(old, new))\nPY"], decision="allow")
